    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>It's Music</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Donald Nawi letter about April 8 article on Handel's Messiah says, in spite of some reservations as a Jew, it s just music (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I am Jewish and have sung Handel's ''Messiah'' as a member of various choral societies more times than I can count, including at Carnegie Hall. For me, it has been and will continue to be the music, just as it is the music when I sing Masses, requiems, magnificats, glorias, passions and other similar works or when I sing with church choirs.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I am Jewish and have sung Handel's ''Messiah'' as a member of various choral societies more times than I can count, including at Carnegie Hall. For me, it has been and will continue to be the music, just as it is the music when I sing Masses, requiems, magnificats, glorias, passions and other similar works or when I sing with church choirs.</p>
        <p>I did wince, however, the first time I sang, from the ''Messiah,'' ''And he shall purify the sons of Levi.'' I was at a rehearsal after the conclusion of Yom Kippur, when I thought I had already been ''purified.''</p>
        <p>Donald Nawi  Scarsdale, N.Y.</p>
        <p>HANDEL AND THE JEWS</p>
      </block>
